cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about compressing and accelerating Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) while retaining their accuracy on classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a mathematical formulation to approximate the standard convolution kernel, which suggests a possible fit for cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper involves machine learning techniques, which could fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could fit into cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
